    Time Keeping

    Timekeeping

    Note: Both supervisors and users can utilize the timekeeping feature. Most time keeping functionalities require a time slice to be enabled, including adding meals,save and release,save and validate,delete, and printing/exporting time data.

    You can use the Timekeeping button to fill the timesheet data by adding time slices. A time slice is the time duration for an activity including lunch. A timesheet is composed of multiple continuous time slices that complete the timesheet for a day's work. As a field technician, you must record the time you spent on each task. You can create time slices in the system to support the work you have completed in the day.

    Adding a Time Slice

    Note: You can only add a timeslice when you have a work order/Trouble Order that is incomplete.

    Users can add time slices for themselves or their crews by navigating to the Timekeeping tab in the IWMS Client application.

    Steps

    The user needs to fill in the fields below inorder to create a time slice:

    Note:Only a few fields are mandatory when creating a time slice.

    AOR Dropdown:Select an AOR

    TaskAction Dropdown:Select a task action.Based on the task action you select, the Task Desc. list is populated

    Task Desc Dropdown:Select a task description. Based on the task description you select, a work order number, if associated, is populated in the WO#/OP# field. Else, you must enter the work order number manually in the (M) WO#/OP# field. If a work order number is entered manually, it means that the entered work order number is not present in the database and is highlighted in the timesheet.

    WO#/OP# field:Type a work order number in the (M) WO#/OP# box.

    PayType Dropdown:Select a pay type.Based on the pay type you select, the A/A Type list is populated.

    A/A Type Dropdown:Select an A/A Type. Based on the pay type you select, the Comp Type list is populated. The Comp Type list is populated when the options selected in the Pay Type list and the A/A Type list are related to compensation.

    From field:Enter a date, and then in the corresponding time list, select a start time for the time slice. By default, today's date is selected.Note: You can create a time slice for the previous six days.

    To field:Enter a date, and then in the corresponding time list, select the end time for the time slice

    Comp Type: Enter the Compensation Type.

    Shift Pay:This is either SW or GR.

    Upgrade code :This is not a compulsory entry.Any timekeeping screen that uses an upgrade code list contains upgrade codes assigned to the logged on role if the upgrade code list is editable.

    seq(MSR#):Enter the Meter Service Request number

    Comment: You can add any remarks here regarding the timeslice.

    Address:Enter the precise Address here

    Note: The dropdown fields CompType and Upgrade Code are disabled because of the filter feature.This is normal behavior.

    2. Click on the Add Time Slice button.

    Observe that a time slice was created as shown below:

    If you are a supervisor creating a time slice for the crew, then;

      1. The Select users page will be displayed.
    • Select the check boxes corresponding to the crew members to be assigned the time slice.
    • Click OK.

    Next to the Add Time Slice button, there is Enable storm override button,Apply to selected Wos button and Reset buttons. Below are their functions:

    Enable storm override

    The Enable Storm Override is a mode. When this mode is switched on, the user working on any task is applied the accounting code as per the Storm Mode. This means, if you are working on a specified task and before that task is complete, if the Storm mode is enabled, though you continue to work on the same task, in the timesheet that task is applied the accounting code as per Storm mode.

    Steps to enable the StormOverride button.

    1. Click on Storm override button
    2. The following screen will appear where you can select either the Standing Work Orders, Capital Work Orders, and Internal Work Orders
    3. Select Show all AOR workorders checkbox to show the full list of available work orders in the selected category. If there are any previous Overrides, select the Previous Override checkbox to view them.
    4. Select a work order on the list(this will auto fill the WO# and OP#) or fill in a specific work order in the WO# and OP# input box.
    5. Select OK to override the work orders in the list.
    6. The Storm override button changes to Disable Storm Override, then the task will appear under the summary tab showing that overriding is set for WO#.

    Apply to selected wos

    You can use this feature to assign the same work order (WO) number to various time slices in a timesheet. You should have an existing timesheet before proceeding the following steps.

    Steps

    To apply the same work order number to selected WOs:

    1. In a timesheet grid, select the check boxes corresponding to the time slices to be assigned the same work order number.You can choose a date range for the timesheets from the open timesheet for date:
    2. In the District list, select an area.
    3. In the Task Action list, select a task action.
    4. Based on the task action you select, the Task Desc list is populated.In the Task Desc list, select a task description.
    5. The (M) WO#/OP# box is made available.In the (M) WO#/OP# box, type a new work order number.
    6. Click Apply to selected WOs.

    The work order number is assigned to all the time slices.

    Reset

    Reset button clears every data that you had previously entered when creating a time slice.

    Copy and paste

    Note: If the timesheet is empty, you'll need to add a regular time slice and select it first (see the guide on Timekeeping for details).

    You can copy and paste time slices in the same timesheet or in the timesheets of other crew members.You can utilize the copy and paste buttons to make work easier.After using the copy button ,only then is the paste button enabled.

    Delete

    Note: If the timesheet is empty, you'll need to add a regular time slice and select it first (see the guide on Timekeeping for details).

    You can delete time slices from a timesheet to remove duplicates or conflicting entries. Once deleted, the time slice is removed from the timesheet.

    Copy crew

    Note: If the timesheet is empty, you'll need to add a regular time slice and select it first (see the guide on Timekeeping for details).The Copy crew button is only enabled to a supervisor with the ability to create and manage crews. Allows you to share the time slice with crew members. Once you copy the crew in a timesheet, the timesheet will be applied to all the crew members.

    Add Comment

    Allows user to add a comment regarding the timeslice/timesheet created.

    Save and validate

    Note:

    If the timesheet is empty, you'll need to add a regular time slice and select it first (see the guide on Timekeeping for details).**

    You can use the Save and Validate icon to save the time slices that you have added in the timesheet and check for any conflicts that need correction. If any conflicts exist in the timesheet, the timesheet cannot be released.

    Save and release

    Note: If the timesheet is empty, you'll need to add a regular time slice and select it first (see the guide on Timekeeping for details). You can use the Save and Release icon to submit the timesheet for approval. A Supervisor can approve the timesheet.

    Adding Meals

    Note: If the timesheet is empty, you'll need to add a regular time slice and select it first (see the guide on Timekeeping for details).

    Users can add meal time slices to their timesheets to account for additional effort beyond mandatory work hours. Multiple meal time slices can be added within a work day.

    Steps to create add a meal
    Select the checkbox corresponding to a time slice in the timesheet.

    1. The Add meal icon is made available.
    2. Click the Add meal icon.
    3. The Meal dialog box is displayed.

    1. In the Start time list, select a start time.
    2. In the End time list, select the end time.
    3. In the A/A Code list, select an A/A code.
    4. Based on the selection, the A/A Reason list is populated.
    5. In the A/A Reason list, select A/A reason.
    6. Click OK.

    The meal time slice is displayed in the timesheet.

    Adding Lunch

    The IWMS Client lets you add a special slice for the lunch break to the timesheet. This Lunch slice isn't tied to any specific billing code or payment. There can only be one Lunch slice per workday.

    Steps to add Lunch

    1. Open the IWMS Client application and go to the Timekeeping section.
    Note: If the timesheet is empty, you'll need to add a regular time slice first (see the guide on Timekeeping for details).**
    1. Click the checkbox next to the time slice you want to add Lunch to. This will enable the Add Lunch icon.
    2. Click the Add Lunch icon.

    Lunch will now be displayed as a separate slice in the timesheet.
